args:
After Gozu Tenno recovers from his injuries,
our heroes make for the Halidom once more.
Seimei then announces that he will defeat
Doman and take the curse upon himself, after
which the party faces off against their foe and
his evil shikigami, Gozu Tenno!
The barrier has been broken, and now I\nwill concentrate this land's mana and\nbegin to create the Underworld Key.
Hot pot'a coffee, Gozu! Yer awake!\nOh, I'm just so dang relieved...
Where do you get off trying to\ndie on me like that?
Forgive me, Lord Seimei; I nearly returned\nto the mana from whence I came without\nfulfilling my part of our vow.

I am fully prepared to go with you into that
black night when next we face Doman,
so please let me atone for allowing your
grandfather to die before my eyes.
Actually, we're good on that point.
I said we're good. No need for you to join\nme in the long dark and blah blah blah.
But if we do not defeat him, we will be\nunable to break the curse of Kodoku.
Well aware, thank you. And I'm still going\nto stop Kodoku, but in a way where no one\nhas to surrender their life.
Well, it's not much of a plan...\nBut I'll make it work.
Haw haw! Yer the best, Lord Seimei—\nand ya better believe this fox'll be\nright behind ya the whole way!
The surrounding mana feels different,\nLord Seimei. Could it be...?
Yes. The barrier is gone, which means we\nneed to move quickly. Are the two of you\nready to do your parts?
Heck yeah! Er, but I reckon the prince'n\nall his pals ain't gonna take kindly to—
Going on without us? No, Seimei,\nwe ain't gonna take kindly to that at all.
You people again? Are you implying I\nshouldn't have left you? You'll only get\nin the way.
In the way, huh? Ha ha!\nThanks, Seimei.
Oh, we got you all figured out, pal!
You went so far as to put up that barrier to\nget us lost in an attempt to keep us from\ngetting involved.
You pretend not to care what happens to\nus, but you actually do. In your heart,\nyou're a kind and decent man.
You're overthinking this so it fits into your\ntwee little narrative. I just didn't want\nyou people slowing me down.
Ha ha! In that case, we'll be sure to fight\nwith you in a manner that won't.
So now what? The barrier around the\nHalidom is down, but can we still avert\nthe incoming crisis?
If we can take down Doman and prevent\nhim from making the Underworld Key,\nthe rest should work itself out.
Then we've got to hurry.\nLet's stop him this time for sure!
This miasma crap goes on forever!
We'll be stopped in our tracks at this rate!

We got us the ability to fight in a group,
so there ain't no reason to be goin' it
alone. What say we all take turns with the
fightin' so no one gets tuckered out?
That makes sense. We'll clear a path\nforward as we keep swapping out the\nfighters on the front line.
We all just have to work together and\ntrust each other! Right, Seimei?

Must you again with the ＂power of
friendship＂ nonsense? *sigh* However,
I must admit that your plan does
possess some advantages.
Happy to help. All right, everyone,\nlet's finish this!
Our scouts send word that Seimei and his\ngroup are fighting their way through the\nshikigami in the forest.
It's only a matter of time now until they\nreach us. Harden defenses at the gate!
It's a bit late in the day to be making\ndefensive preparations, don't you think?\nYou really aren't very good at this.
Hail, Yoshitsune. Do you come to us\nwith any new information?
Oh, most definitely: The vanguard of the\nTwelve Wyrmclans has arrived.
You wretch! You would turn on us now?!
Turn on you? I never JOINED you—though\nthat doesn't mean I'm on the side of the\nWyrmclans, either.
I just want to meet your boss so I can\nfinally be shed of this immortal body.
I'm done playing herald. Go ahead,\nSeimei. Oh, and do make it flashy.
Make this a fight so grand that it brings\nher running...
It ends here, Doman! I won't let you ruin\nAlberia's mana for your own greed!
Well, well. The gang's all here.\nDecided to die together then, Seimei?
Nope. Decided it'll be just you who dies.
Are you quite sure of that? If you're the\nonly one left alive, Kodoku will rise\nand you will bear an immense curse.
Fully aware. Don't give a damn.
You want me to write it down so you can\nread it slowly? I'm not dying with you.
I'm going to take that curse of yours\nupon myself, and I'm going to live.
Ah, now THIS is interesting! A new choice\npresents itself! But do you think you can\ntruly withstand it?
You will be filled with unspeakable power,\nand yet suffer from the horrors of the curse\nfor the rest of your days.
Like I said a second ago, very well aware.\nSee, the thing is, I didn't think of anything\nbut breaking the Kodoku curse before now.
I thought it was my responsibility to die\nand end the curse that I discovered,\nbut now I've changed my mind.
Even if it means I have to roll through life\nwith a curse, I need to stay in this world a\nlittle longer.
Aaaah ha ha ha! Excellent! So excellent!\nNow that you wish to live, we can clash\nwith TRUE murderous intent!
This land's mana is now suffused\nwith the power of Yomi...
And with that power, I can lift my\nfell onmyodo—AND the power of my\nshikigami—to the ultimate level!
Now, Seimei, I am my ultimate self...\nLet me see what YOU can become!
Dammit, it's that shakin...shooka...\nshushly... Whatever! It's that thing!
I'll return this knock-off dragon of yours\nto paper and burn it to ash!
Be careful! The shikigami's power\nhas increased considerably!
We'll beat it anyway and take it all back.\nOur home, Seimei's past... All of it!
